==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Eocene
<hw>E"o*cene</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>'hw`s</grk>
daybreak, dawn + <?/ new, recent.]</ety> <fld>(Geol.)</fld>
<def>Pertaining to the first in time of the three subdivisions into
which the Tertiary formation is divided by geologists, and alluding to
the approximation in its life to that of the present era; <as>as,
<ex>Eocene</ex> deposits</as>.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>The
Eocene formation.</def></def2> <rj><au>Lyell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

